solely as innocent victims. Unsettling fixed categories, Baldwin's essays construct a theory of race consciousness that captures the effects of racial identity in everyday experience.Balfour persuasively reads Baldwin's work alongside that of W. E. B. Du Bois to accentuate how double consciousness works differently on either side of the color line. She contends that the allusiveness and incompleteness of Baldwin's essays sustains the tension between general claims about American racial history and the singularity of individual experiences. The Evidence of Things Not Said establishes Baldwin's contributions to democratic theory and situates him as an indispensable voice in contemporary debates about racial injustice.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aAfrican Americans in literature. 0aAfrican AmericansxPolitics and government. 0aPolitical fiction, AmericanxHistory and criticism. 0aPolitics and literaturezUnited StatesxHistory and criticism. 4aPhilosophy. 4aPolitical Science & Political History. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Political ideologies / Democracy.2bisacsh  aafroamerican research.  aamerican racial history.  aanalysis of james baldwin.  abeauford delaney.  ablack authors.  acritical insights and approaches to Baldwin's essays.  ademocracy in literature.  ademocratic ideals and racial history.  ademocratic theory.  aessays on james baldwin.  aessays on racism.  aharlem renaissance.  ahow to be antiracist.  ajames baldwin racial identity.  ajames baldwin racial writings.  ajames baldwin scholar.  ajames baldwin social criticism.  ajames baldwin.  aliterary criticism.  aliterary political theory.  anotes of a native son.  apolitical fiction.  apolitical philosophy.  apolitical theorists.  apolitical theory curriculum.  apolitical theory.  apolitical writi